THE SYSTEM, SPANNING
SOME ONE AND A HALF

00:25:46.160 --> 00:25:48.830
MILLION ACRES,
HAS ENDURED MUCH,

00:25:48.830 --> 00:25:51.230
LOSING 50% OF ITS WATER
FLOW TO NEIGHBORING

00:25:51.230 --> 00:25:54.530
AGRICULTURAL ACTIVITY AND
BURGEONING DEVELOPMENT.

00:25:54.530 --> 00:25:57.230
BUT CONFRONTING SOUTH
FLORIDA TODAY THERE'S THE

00:25:57.230 --> 00:26:01.400
OVER-ARCHING ENVIRONMENTAL
PROBLEM - GLOBAL WARMING.

00:26:01.400 --> 00:26:03.700
YES, GLOBAL WARMING
IS VERY REAL.

00:26:03.700 --> 00:26:06.000
AND IT'S NOT SOMETHING
FOR THE FUTURE;

00:26:06.000 --> 00:26:08.160
IT'S IN FACT
HAPPENING NOW.

00:26:08.160 --> 00:26:12.030
AND, YES, IT WILL HAVE
AN INCREASING INFLUENCE

00:26:12.030 --> 00:26:14.500
ON THE EVERGLADES AND
ALL OF OUR COASTAL

00:26:14.500 --> 00:26:17.130
AND LOW-LYING
ENVIRONMENTS.

00:26:17.130 --> 00:26:19.400
THE POLAR ICE
CAPS ARE MELTING

00:26:19.400 --> 00:26:21.360
AS OUR PLANET
HEATS UP.

00:26:21.360 --> 00:26:25.330
THAT SPELLS DANGER FOR LOW
LYING AREAS AROUND THE GLOBE.

00:26:25.330 --> 00:26:27.900
ESPECIALLY TROUBLING
TO SCIENTISTS

00:26:27.900 --> 00:26:30.260
OBSERVING CHANGE
IN SOUTH FLORIDA

00:26:30.260 --> 00:26:33.800
IS A DRAMATICALLY EVOLVING
LANDSCAPE ALONG THE COAST.

00:26:33.800 --> 00:26:37.030
WE'RE BEGINNING TO SEE
DRAMATIC CHANGES IN THE

00:26:37.030 --> 00:26:40.130
BOUNDARY BETWEEN THE
MANGROVE AND WHATEVER'S

00:26:40.130 --> 00:26:44.500
BEHIND THEM - EITHER WATER
OR FRESHWATER SWAMP.

00:26:44.500 --> 00:26:48.160
AND ALL OF THIS IS BECAUSE,
FOR SOUTH FLORIDA,

00:26:48.160 --> 00:26:50.660
FOR INSTANCE, WE
HAVE HAD A RELATIVE

00:26:50.660 --> 00:26:53.900
SEA LEVEL RISE OF NINE
TO TEN INCHES SINCE 1930.

00:26:53.900 --> 00:26:57.130
THIS IS AN INCREASE IN THE
RATE OF SEA LEVEL RISE OF

00:26:57.130 --> 00:27:00.200
EIGHT TO NINE TIMES WHAT
HAD BEEN GOING ON FOR THE

00:27:00.200 --> 00:27:03.300
LAST 2000 YEARS AND
THAT'S DRAMATIC -

00:27:03.300 --> 00:27:06.660
IT'S CLOSE
TO CATASTROPHIC.

00:27:06.660 --> 00:27:10.030
IN THE NEXT 100 YEARS, IF
SOMETHING ISN'T DONE TO

00:27:10.030 --> 00:27:12.600
LIMIT AND LOWER GLOBAL
WARMING POLLUTION,

00:27:12.600 --> 00:27:15.660
EARTH'S SEAS WILL
CONTINUE TO RISE,

00:27:15.660 --> 00:27:19.630
ACCORDING TO DR. WANLESS,
BY ANOTHER TWO FEET.

00:27:19.630 --> 00:27:22.030
PARK OFFICIALS
ARE CONCERNED.

00:27:22.030 --> 00:27:25.630
I'M CONCERNED ABOUT SEA
LEVEL RISE SINCE RELIEF

00:27:25.630 --> 00:27:28.630
HERE IS SO LOW, WE'RE
SEEING AREAS THAT WOULD,

00:27:28.630 --> 00:27:30.700
IN FACT, BE INUNDATED
AND CHANGE OF HABITAT

00:27:30.700 --> 00:27:32.700
FROM SAW GRASS
PRAIRIE TO MORE

00:27:32.700 --> 00:27:35.730
MANGROVE SALT-DOMINATED
ECOSYSTEMS.

00:27:35.730 --> 00:27:40.300
ACROSS FLORIDA BAY, MUCH
DAMAGE HAS ALREADY BEEN DONE.

00:27:40.300 --> 00:27:43.900
NOW ADD ANOTHER
TWO FEET OF SEA.

00:27:43.900 --> 00:27:46.800
THE REDRAWN COASTLINE
SPELLS SIGNIFICANT LOSS

00:27:46.800 --> 00:27:49.200
OF WETLAND HABITAT
FOR WADING BIRDS

00:27:49.200 --> 00:27:51.600
AND FRESHWATER AQUATICS.

00:27:51.600 --> 00:27:54.600
GLOBAL WARMING
MEANS RISING SEAS,

00:27:54.600 --> 00:27:56.330
RISING TEMPERATURES,

00:27:56.330 --> 00:27:59.360
AND RISING UNCERTAINTY
ABOUT THE WEATHER.

00:27:59.360 --> 00:28:02.330
SCIENTISTS ARE CONCERNED
ABOUT THE INCREASED HEAT

00:28:02.330 --> 00:28:06.060
RISING OFF THE OCEANS AND
INTENSIFYING HURRICANES.

00:28:06.060 --> 00:28:09.000
THIS YEAR, WITH HURRICANES
KATRINA AND WILMA,

00:28:09.000 --> 00:28:10.960
IN BOTH THOSE
CASES WE EXPERIENCED

00:28:10.960 --> 00:28:14.630
A STORM SURGE HERE AT
EVERGLADES NATIONAL PARK.

00:28:14.630 --> 00:28:18.160
IN KATRINA WE HAD A STORM
SURGE DOWN IN FLAMINGO

00:28:18.160 --> 00:28:20.760
THAT WAS FROM THREE
TO FOUR FEET

00:28:20.760 --> 00:28:23.760
AND THEN SIX WEEKS
LATER, IN WILMA,

00:28:23.760 --> 00:28:26.800
WE HAD A STORM SURGE OF
FROM EIGHT TO NINE FEET.

00:28:26.800 --> 00:28:31.030
AND I AM CONCERNED THAT
INCREASES IN SEA LEVEL RISE

00:28:31.030 --> 00:28:34.100
WOULD EXACERBATE
THOSE KINDS OF IMPACTS.

00:28:34.100 --> 00:28:37.900
EVEN IF THE HURRICANE
LEVEL STAYS THE SAME,

00:28:37.900 --> 00:28:40.500
WITH RISING SEA
LEVEL WE WILL HAVE

00:28:40.500 --> 00:28:44.200
AN INCREASED IMPACT
BY HURRICANES

00:28:44.200 --> 00:28:46.460
BECAUSE THEY WILL
REACH FURTHER IN,

00:28:46.460 --> 00:28:48.560
THEY WILL MOVE MORE
SAND ON BARRIER ISLANDS,

00:28:48.560 --> 00:28:50.800
THEY WILL CUT MORE
INLETS, AND SO ON.

00:28:50.800 --> 00:28:53.830
AND SO, EVEN WITHOUT
WORRYING ABOUT THE INCREASE

00:28:53.830 --> 00:28:58.300
- LIKELY, IN MY MIND -
INCREASE IN HURRICANES,

00:28:58.300 --> 00:29:00.600
WE'RE STILL GOING TO
HAVE A DRAMATICALLY

00:29:00.600 --> 00:29:04.000
INCREASED INFLUENCE
FROM HURRICANES.

00:29:04.000 --> 00:29:07.400
SOUTH FLORIDA, ITSELF
AN ANCIENT CORAL REEF,

00:29:07.400 --> 00:29:09.760
CONNECTS TO THE
COUNTRY'S ONLY LIVING

00:29:09.760 --> 00:29:11.930
BARRIER REEF
ENVIRONMENT.

00:29:11.930 --> 00:29:15.800
HAVING LOGGED OVER 18,000
DIVE HOURS IN THESE WATERS,

00:29:15.800 --> 00:29:19.400
DR. BILLY CAUSEY TREASURES
THE FLORIDA KEYS.

00:29:19.400 --> 00:29:22.100
THE KEYS ARE AN
INCREDIBLY SPECIAL PLACE.

