SCIENTISTS ARE CERTAIN
THAT THERE ARE CHANGES

00:30:19.330 --> 00:30:22.400
TAKING PLACE, CLIMATE
CHANGES THAT WE ARE

00:30:22.400 --> 00:30:24.030
ABLE TO RECORD.

00:30:24.030 --> 00:30:26.230
WE'RE SEEING THIS IN THE
CORAL REEF ENVIRONMENT -

00:30:26.230 --> 00:30:28.600
THE CORAL REEFS ARE REALLY
THE CANARY IN THE COALMINE

00:30:28.600 --> 00:30:32.130
IN THAT WE ARE SEEING
CHANGES TAKE PLACE.

00:30:32.130 --> 00:30:35.060
FROZEN ICE CAPS OF THE
ARCTIC AND ANTARCTIC

00:30:35.060 --> 00:30:38.130
AND CORAL REEFS TOGETHER
REPRESENT THE MOST

00:30:38.130 --> 00:30:41.830
STABLE ENVIRONMENTS
IN GEOLOGIC TIME.

